    "Table tuningTable tuning, short for table instruction tuning, constructs instruction tuning datasets by leveraging multiple existing table-related datasets.",
    "The instruction tuning dataset can be in the form of (Instruction, Table, Output).",
    "Figure 6 is an example entry from TableInstruct, the instruction tuning dataset for TableLlama [11].",
    "In this example, the Instruction specifies the task; theTable describes table content, table metadata, or task-specific content.",
    "The Output features natural language outputs like table QA answers, text from table-totext transformations, result tables after manipulation, or a mix of text and tables."
